race.comment: POWERBOUND (1) doesn't win many but looks to have found a suitable race. He was outclassed two back in a strong BM78 won by Guerite who went on to win the Country Final at Flemington. The last run at Donald was good, getting home strongly late in a dash home. This is easier again and he draws for a soft trail. LYGON STREET LUIGI (5) is another that struggles to win, stuck on the 1 victory from 26 starts, but can certainly find one better with 10 runner-up finishes, including last start when beaten a nose at Pakenham. He can cross up from out wide and might just get the head done first. HOUDINI (3) resumes. Last seen running in a strong 3yo race behind Taken reads well. He's a capable type who can win this fresh. SALCHOW (6) got home well fresh here over 1307m and will be better suited to this trip second up. This is easier.
